%3EIf%20you're%20aiming%20to%20retire%20at%20the%20standard%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhen-can-i-retire%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAmerica%2527s%2520official%2520retirement%2520age%2520%25E2%2580%2594%2520when%2Ckick%2520in%2520at%2520age%252065.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eage%20of%2065%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20buckle%20up%20because%20you're%20going%20to%20want%20to%20hear%20this%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20a%20simulated%20model%20that%20factors%20in%20things%20like%20changes%20in%20health%2C%20nursing%20home%20costs%2C%20and%20demographics%2C%20about%2045%25%20of%20Americans%20who%20leave%20the%20workforce%20at%2065%20are%20likely%20to%20run%20out%20of%20money%20during%20retirement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20model%2C%20run%20by%20Morningstar's%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20and%20Policy%20Studies%2C%20showed%20that%20the%20risk%20is%20higher%20for%20single%20women%2C%20who%20had%20a%2055%25%20chance%20of%20running%20out%20of%20money%20versus%2040%25%20for%20single%20men%20and%2041%25%20for%20couples.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20group%20most%20susceptible%20to%20ending%20up%20in%20this%20situation%20are%20those%20who%20didn't%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esave%20toward%20a%20retirement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20plan%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D279c10f5695205075dc5969e1b1901ab9fa298bd950dc41b893dc369d54fc79b%26postID%3D66f42a530c43543ec796d51f%26postSlug%3Dretirement-saving-why-half-retirees-could-run-out-of-money-2024-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.morningstar.com%252Fnews%252Fmarketwatch%252F20240803255%252Falmost-half-of-those-who-retire-at-65-could-run-out-of-money%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccording%20to%20Spencer%20Look%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20center's%20associate%20director.%20Still%2C%20retirement%20advisors%20say%20even%20those%20who%20think%20they're%20prepared%20aren't.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20a%20big%20problem%2C%20says%20JoePat%20Roop%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Belmont%20Capital%20Advisors%2C%20who%20has%20been%20helping%20clients%20set%20up%20income%20streams%20for%20their%20retirement%20years.%20What%20might%20surprise%20many%20is%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20mistakes%20people%20make%20isn't%20so%20much%20about%20how%20much%20they%20save%20but%20how%20they%20plan%20around%20what%20they%20save.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20be%20more%20specific%2C%20Roop%20says%20what%20catches%20retirees%20off%20guard%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3Etaxes%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20planning%20around%20them%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Many%20assume%20they%20will%20be%20in%20a%20lower%20tax%20bracket%20once%20they%20stop%20receiving%20a%20paycheck.%20But%20from%20his%20experience%2C%20retirees%20often%20remain%20in%20the%20same%20tax%20bracket%20or%20could%20even%20end%20up%20in%20a%20higher%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20wrong%20in%20so%20many%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Roop%20said.%20After%20retiring%2C%20most%20people's%20spending%20habits%20either%20remain%20the%20same%20or%20go%20up.%20When%20you%20have%20more%20leisure%20time%20on%20your%20hands%2C%20more%20money%20goes%20toward%20entertainment%20and%20travel%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20retirement.%20The%20outcome%20is%20a%20higher%20withdrawal%20rate%2C%20which%20can%20push%20you%20into%20a%20higher%20tax%20bracket%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20spend%20their%20careers%20investing%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E401(k)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-ira-accounts%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUnlike%2520401(k)s%2520and%2Cunlock%2520even%2520more%2520tax%2520advantages.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIRA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20they%20allow%20contributions%20before%20taxes.%20It%20sounds%20like%20a%20great%20perk%20when%20you%20can%20cut%20your%20taxes%20and%20defer%20them.%20The%20downside%20is%20that%20withdrawals%20will%20be%20taxed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20solution%20is%20to%20add%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20an%20after-tax%20account%20that%20allows%20gains%20to%20grow%20tax-free.%20This%20way%2C%20during%20a%20year%20when%20you%20need%20to%20withdraw%20a%20higher%20amount%2C%20you%20can%20resort%20to%20that%20account%20instead%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20big%20mistake%20people%20make%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3Emoving%20money%20around%20in%20an%20inefficient%20way%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20leads%20them%20to%20incur%20more%20taxes%20than%20they%20should%20or%20lose%20on%20future%20returns.%20This%20can%20include%20choosing%20to%20withdraw%20a%20high%20amount%20of%20money%20from%20an%20investment%20account%20to%20pay%20off%20a%20mortgage%20or%20buy%20a%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20rules%20that%20the%20IRS%20has%20set%20up%20for%20us%2C%20and%20they're%20there%20to%20pay%20the%20government%2C%20not%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Roop%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20prime%20example%20of%20a%20big%20tax%20mistake%20one%20of%20Roop's%20clients%20(let's%20call%20him%20Bob)%20made%20recently%20was%20liquidating%20part%20of%20an%20IRA%20to%20buy%20a%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBob%20is%20a%20man%20of%20modest%20means%20retiring%20this%20year%2C%20Roop%20said.%20But%20a%20sudden%20breakup%20with%20his%20girlfriend%20led%20him%20to%20cash%20out%20some%20of%20his%20IRA%20to%20buy%20a%20house.%20He%20decided%20to%20withhold%20the%20tax%2C%20which%20could%20have%20been%20between%20%2430%2C000%20and%20%2440%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20he%20told%20us%20this%2C%20my%20mouth%20dropped%2C%26quot%3B%20Roop%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20Bob%2C%20you%20had%20the%20money%20for%20the%20down%20payment%20in%20another%20account%20where%20there%20would've%20been%20no%20tax%2C%20and%20we%20were%20going%20to%20roll%20over%20your%20IRA%20and%20put%20it%20in%20a%20tax-deferred%20account.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20Roop%20planned%20to%20move%20money%20from%20Bob's%20IRA%20to%20an%20annuity%20that%20would%20have%20paid%20him%20a%20bonus%20of%2010%25%2C%20or%20%2415%2C000.%20The%20mistake%20might%20cost%20Bob%20between%20%2445%2C000%20and%20%2455%2C000%2C%20between%20the%20owed%20taxes%20and%20the%20missed%20bonus.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lesson%3A%20don't%20be%20Bob.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20big%20mistake%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3Esequence%20risk%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20is%20when%20you%20withdraw%20from%20your%20portfolio%20when%20the%20stock%20market%20is%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20averaged%20close%20to%2010%25%20for%20the%20last%2050%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Roop%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20it's%20a%20true%20assumption%20that%20over%20the%20next%2050%20years%2C%20it'll%20probably%20make%20between%20nine%20and%2011%25.%20But%20when%20people%20retire%2C%20we%20don't%20know%20the%20sequence%20of%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimply%20put%2C%20if%20you%20retire%20next%20year%20with%20an%20investment%20portfolio%20worth%20a%20million%20dollars%20and%20the%20market%20drops%20by%2015%25%20that%20year%2C%20you%20now%20have%20%24850%2C000.%20If%20you%20need%20to%20withdraw%20during%20that%20time%2C%20it%20will%20be%20very%20difficult%20to%20get%20back%20to%20breakeven%2C%20Roop%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20means%20that%20owning%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20isn't%20enough%20diversification.%20He%20noted%20that%20you%20must%20also%20have%20something%20that%20is%20principal-protected%2C%20such%20as%20a%20CD%2C%20fixed%20annuities%2C%20or%20government%20bond.%20This%20way%2C%20you%20can%20avoid%20touching%20your%20portfolio%20during%20a%20bad%20time%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGil%20Baumgarten%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Segment%20Wealth%20Management%2C%20says%20another%20big%20reason%20he%20sees%20people%20run%20out%20of%20money%20is%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3Elack%20of%20appropriate%20risk-taking%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20they%20make%20during%20their%20income-earning%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20low-risk%20approach%20is%20earning%20interest%20on%20cash%2C%20a%20terrible%20form%20of%20compounding%20because%20it's%20taxed%20higher%20than%20ordinary%20income%20with%20lower%20returns%2C%20he%20noted.%20Meanwhile%2C%20stocks%20could%20see%20higher%20returns%20and%20aren't%20taxed%20until%20sold%2C%20or%20aren't%20taxed%20at%20all%20if%20you%20opt%20for%20a%20Roth%20IRA.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20take%20into%20account%20how%20expensive%20things%20get%20over%20time%2C%20not%20realizing%20that%20they%20can%20live%20another%2040%20years%20in%20retirement.%20You%20can't%20get%20rich%20investing%20your%20money%20at%205%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Baumgarten%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20for%20those%20who%20do%20take%20risks%2C%20it's%20often%20the%20wrong%20kind.%20They%20chase%20hype%20and%20bet%20on%20highly%20speculative%20investments.%20They%20end%20up%20losing%20money%20and%20assume%20risk%20is%20bad%2C%20Baumgarten%20said.%20The%20right%20kind%20of%20risk%20is%20a%20higher%20exposure%20to%20stocks%20through%20mutual%20funds%20or%20index%20funds%20and%20even%20buying%20blue%20chip%20stocks%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-why-half-retirees-could-run-out-of-money-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727282971000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f42e0bcfb7f307e574cf7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-why-half-retirees-could-run-out-of-money-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It's%20less%20about%20how%20much%20you%20save%20and%20more%20about%20how%20you%20move%20money.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-why-half-retirees-could-run-out-of-money-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prime%20Video%20France%20Unveils%20Sexy%20Originals%2C%20Rebecca%20Zlotowski%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Glamsquad%3B%E2%80%9D2be3%E2%80%B2%20Series%20on%20French%20Boys%20Band%3B%E2%80%99%20Pickup%20of%20%E2%80%98Escort%20Boys%E2%80%99%20Season%202%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727282724000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FCulte-2Be3_1.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236155433%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon%20Prime%20Video%20France%20has%20unveiled%20its%20slate%20of%20new%20originals%20and%20co-production%20titles%2C%20ranging%20from%20series%2C%20movies%20and%20unscripted%20shows.%20These%20include%20some%20sexy%2C%20comedic%20and%20action-packed%20titles%20such%20as%20