erming%20as%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20objectionable%26quot%3B%20the%20observation%20made%20by%20a%20high%20court%20about%20make-up%20articles%20and%20a%20widow%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20such%20a%20comment%20was%20not%20commensurate%20with%20the%20sensitivity%20and%20neutrality%20expected%20from%20a%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20dealing%20with%20the%20appeals%20filed%20against%20a%20verdict%20of%20the%20Patna%20High%20Court%20in%20a%20murder%20case%20of%201985%20in%20which%20a%20woman%20was%20abducted%20and%20later%20killed%2C%20allegedly%20to%20obtain%20possession%20of%20a%20house%20belonging%20to%20her%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20had%20upheld%20the%20conviction%20of%20five%20persons%20in%20the%20case%20and%20had%20set%20aside%20the%20acquittal%20of%20two%20other%20co-accused.%20It%20had%20convicted%20the%20two%20persons%2C%20who%20were%20earlier%20acquitted%20of%20all%20charges%20by%20a%20trial%20court%2C%20and%20sentenced%20them%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Bela%20M%20Trivedi%20and%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%20noted%20the%20high%20court%20had%20examined%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20victim%20was%20actually%20residing%20in%20the%20house%20from%20where%20she%20was%20alleged%20to%20have%20been%20abducted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20relying%20on%20the%20testimonies%20of%20the%20maternal%20uncle%20and%20brother-in-law%20of%20the%20woman%20as%20well%20as%20the%20investigating%20officer%20(IO)%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20concluded%20that%20the%20victim%20was%20residing%20in%20the%20said%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20the%20IO%20had%20inspected%20the%20house%20and%20no%20direct%20material%2C%20except%20some%20make-up%20articles%2C%20could%20be%20gathered%20to%20indicate%20that%20the%20victim%20was%20actually%20residing%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20admittedly%2C%20another%20woman%2C%20who%20was%20a%20widow%2C%20was%20also%20residing%20in%20the%20same%20portion%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20the%20high%20court%20did%20take%20note%20of%20this%20fact%20but%20explained%20it%20away%20by%20observing%20that%20since%20the%20other%20woman%20was%20a%20widow%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20make-up%20articles%20could%20not%20have%20belonged%20to%20her%20as%20there%20was%20no%20need%20for%20her%20to%20put%20on%20make-up%2C%20being%20a%20widow%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20opinion%2C%20the%20observation%20of%20the%20high%20court%20is%20not%20only%20legally%20untenable%20but%20also%20highly%20objectionable.%20A%20sweeping%20observation%20of%20this%20nature%20is%20not%20commensurate%20with%20the%20sensitivity%20and%20neutrality%20expected%20from%20a%20court%20of%20law%2C%20specifically%20when%20the%20same%20is%20not%20made%20out%20from%20any%20evidence%20on%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20mere%20presence%20of%20certain%20make-up%20articles%20cannot%20be%20conclusive%20proof%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20woman%20was%20residing%20in%20the%20house%2C%20especially%20when%20another%20woman%20was%20admittedly%20residing%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20make-up%20articles%20were%20linked%20with%20the%20deceased%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20completely%20unacceptable%20reasoning%20and%20without%20any%20corroborative%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20no%20personal%20belongings%20of%20the%20woman%20such%20as%20clothes%20and%20footwear%20could%20be%20found%20in%20the%20entire%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20victim%20had%20died%20in%20August%201985%20in%20Munger%20district%20and%20a%20report%20was%20lodged%20by%20her%20brother-in-law%20that%20she%20was%20abducted%20by%20seven%20persons%20from%20their%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20an%20FIR%20was%20lodged%20and%20later%2C%20a%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20against%20seven%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20court%20had%20convicted%20five%20accused%20for%20commission%20of%20offences%2C%20including%20that%20of%20murder%20while%20the%20other%20two%20were%20acquitted%20of%20all%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20there%20was%20no%20direct%20evidence%20on%20record%20to%20prove%20the%20commission%20of%20murder%20by%20the%20accused%20persons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20regards%20motive%2C%20we%20may%20suffice%20to%20say%20that%20motive%20has%20a%20bearing%20only%20when%20the%20evidence%20on%20record%20is%20sufficient%20to%20prove%20the%20ingredients%20of%20the%20offences%20under%20consideration.%20Without%20the%20proof%20of%20foundational%20facts%2C%20the%20case%20of%20the%20prosecution%20cannot%20succeed%20on%20the%20presence%20of%20motive%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20acquitted%20the%20seven%20accused%20of%20all%20the%20charges%20and%20directed%20that%20they%20be%20released%20forthwith%2C%20if%20in%20custody.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727280000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fg7424rfo_supreme-court_625x300_24_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhighly-objectionable-supreme-court-on-high-courts-remark-on-widow-make-up-6648617%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Terming%20as%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20objectionable%26quot%3B%20the%20observation%20made%20by%20a%20high%20court%20about%20make-up%20articles%20and%20a%20widow%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20such%20a%20comment%20was%20not%20commensurate%20with%20the%20sensitivity%20and%20neutrality%20expected%20from%20a%20cou