4420%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20number%20of%20people%20working%20part-time%20but%20say%20they%20would%20rather%20work%20full-time%20is%20rising.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20labor%20differential%20between%20those%20who%20think%20jobs%20are%20plentiful%20versus%20hard%20to%20get%20is%20falling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20are%20usually%20early%20signs%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20BCA%20Research%20strategist%20Peter%20Berezin%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20data%20shows%20easing%20inflation%20and%20a%20steady%20decline%20in%20jobless%20claims%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20but%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20the%20economy%20aren't%20out%20of%20the%20woods%2C%20BCA%20Research%20says.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm's%20chief%20global%20strategist%2C%20Peter%20Berezin%2C%20pointed%20to%20two%20low-key%20labor%20market%20indicators%20flashing%20warning%20signals%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20working%20part%20time%20but%20would%20rather%20be%20working%20full%20time%2C%20has%20%26quot%3Bstarted%20rising%20meaningfully%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said%20in%20a%20Monday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20rose%20to%204.83%20million%20in%20August%2C%20an%20almost%206%25%20increase%20from%20July%20and%20an%20almost%2017%25%20increase%20from%20the%20year%20prior%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.t08.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20released%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20that%20number%20has%20always%20increased%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20Berezin%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCould%20this%20time%20be%20different%3F%20I%20am%20open%20to%20the%20idea.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20onus%20is%20on%20the%20soft%20landers%20to%20show%20why.%20So%20far%2C%20I%20have%20not%20seen%20any%20convincing%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20recent%20survey%20data%20shows%20a%20narrowing%20gap%20in%20positive%20and%20negative%20labor%20market%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20differential%2C%20which%20measures%20those%20who%20think%20jobs%20are%20plentiful%20versus%20those%20who%20think%20they%20are%20hard%20to%20get%2C%20fell%203.3%20points%20to%2012.6%20in%20September%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.conference-board.org%2Ftopics%2Fconsumer-confidence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Conference%20Board%20released%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20%26quot%3Bwell%20below%26quot%3B%20pre-pandemic%20numbers%2C%20and%20below%20the%202019%20average%20of%2033.2%2C%20Berezin%20said%20in%20a%20Tuesday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20the%20peak%20in%20the%20labor%20differential%20comes%20nine%20months%20ahead%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20Berezin%20says.%20But%20this%20time%20around%2C%20its%20flashing%20closer%20to%20a%20rapid%20slowdown%20as%20the%20labor%20market%20pivots%20to%20showing%20weak%20labor%20demand%20via%20higher%20unemployment%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20slower%20wage%20growth%20and%20lower%20job%20openings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20suspect%20that%20it%20has%20taken%20much%20longer%20this%20time%20around%20because%20until%20recently%2C%20the%20economy%20was%20operating%20along%20the%20steep%20side%20of%20the%20labor%20supply%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20warning%20signs%20come%20two%20months%20after%20Berezin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-crash-prediction-2025-decline-fed-fails-avoid-recession-2024-7%3F_gl%3D1*19uo0cc*_ga*MTY3OTgyNjg0MS4xNzIxMDE2MDM2*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcyNzI2OTMwOC4xODMuMS4xNzI3MjcwMzIyLjE1LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecautioned%20investors%20over%20a%20coming%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20hit%20the%20US%20economy%20later%20this%20year%20or%20early%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20seems%20to%20be%20sticking%20with%20that%20prediction%2C%20despite%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20told%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20strong%20and%20that%20the%20recent%20rise%20in%20unemployment%20reflects%20positive%20developments%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20that%20more%20people%20are%20joining%20the%20labor%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20the%20data%20points%20to%20the%20contrary%2C%20with%20a%20slowdown%20in%20year-over-year%20labor%20force%20growth%20from%201.9%25%20a%20year%20ago%20to%200.4%25%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20is%20it%20that%20all%20these%20new%20joiners%20were%20able%20to%20easily%20find%20jobs%20back%20then%20but%20cannot%20do%20so%20now%3F%20The%20only%20plausible%20answer%20is%20that%20labor%20demand%20has%20slowed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20most%20of%20that%20increase%20in%20unemployment%20comes%20from%20people%20losing%20their%20jobs.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20unemployed%20because%20they%20lost%20their%20job%20has%20risen%20by%200.21%20percentage%20points%20from%20a%2012-month%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20history%20is%20any%20indication%2C%20that%20rise%20likely%20points%20to%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20has%20never%20been%20a%20case%20over%20the%20past%2050%20years%20where%20this%20metric%20has%20increased%20by%20more%20than%200.20%20percentage%20points%20without%20a%20recession%20occurring%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-market-indicators-recession-warning-signs-bca-research-berezin-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727277976000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b50c395da406397bf44420%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%