0some%20fiber%2C%20all%20of%20which%20help%20to%20slow%20digestion%20for%20fewer%20blood%20sugar%20fluctuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20keeps%20me%20full%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20it%20sets%20me%20off%20on%20a%20nice%20path%20of%20gentle%20undulating%20hills%20of%20glucose.%20You%20don't%20want%20these%20mountains%20and%20these%20ravines%2C%20for%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20Berry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce09e23b-658b-4d26-8413-2b47b790eb19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20still%20makes%20time%20to%20enjoy%20food%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20hasn't%20cut%20out%20carbs%20or%20treats%20completely%2C%20and%20said%20it's%20not%20realistic%20to%20expect%20blood%20sugar%20to%20be%20a%20perfectly%20flat%20or%20balanced%20throughout%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20increase%20in%20circulating%20blood%20sugar%20is%20a%20normal%20physiological%20response%20to%20eating%20carbohydrate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20bodies%20are%20made%20to%20be%20able%20to%20handle%20changes%20in%20circulations%20of%20blood%20glucose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20is%20moderation%2C%20and%20to%20find%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.insider.com%2Fstory%2F66f189a8d738168e48a49bf3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20ways%20to%20enjoy%20carbs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20foods%20without%20extremes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20food%20is%20too%20healthy%20to%20be%20enjoyed%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20healthy%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20also%20means%20making%20compromises%2C%20and%20making%20choices%20that%20work%20best%20for%20your%20lifestyle.%20For%20instance%2C%20there's%20some%20evidence%20that%20eating%20late%20at%20night%20can%20prompt%20a%20bigger%20blood%20sugar%20response%2C%20but%20Berry%20said%20it's%20worth%20it%20to%20have%20dinner%20with%20her%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20remember%20food%20is%20part%20of%20our%20culture%2C%20our%20emotion