0nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F09%2F20%2Fasia%2Fsouth-korea-abortion-youtube-video-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Seoul%20National%20Police%20began%20investigating%20the%20woman%20in%20July%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20government%20after%20she%20posted%20a%20video%20to%20YouTube%20purportedly%20documenting%20her%20experience%20of%20getting%20an%20abortion%2C%20cops%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20abortions%20past%2024%20weeks%20are%20banned%20in%20many%20jurisdictions%2C%20or%20reserved%20for%20very%20exceptional%20cases.%20However%2C%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20there%20are%20no%20laws%20governing%20when%2C%20where%20or%20how%20abortions%20can%20take%20place.%20But%20this%20was%20not%20always%20the%20case.%20For%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20policy%20vacuum.%20Before%20this%2C%20strict%20laws%20governing%20the%20medical%20procedure%20made%20abortion%20a%20crime%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%20two%20years%20in%20prison.%20It%20only%20limited%20exceptions%20for%20rape%2C%20incest%2C%20and%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20life%2C%20health%20of%20the%20mother%20or%20the%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%202019%20that%20South%20Korea's%20Constitutional%20Court%20overturned%20the%20ban%2C%20giving%20the%20National%20Assembly%20until%20the%20end%20of%202020%20to%20enact%20new%20abortion%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20court%20recommended%20should%20include%20a%20term%20limit%20of%2022%20weeks.%20When%20the%20legislature%20failed%20to%20meet%20that%20deadline%2C%20the%20criminal%20provisions%20around%20abortion%20expired%2C%20effectively%20legalising%20abortion%20at%20any%20stage%20of%20pregnancy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fplease-forgive-me-elon-musk-after-billionaire-vinod-khosla-demands-apology-for-spreading-false-claims-6646580%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B