%20with%20employees%20from%20organisations%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F331893%2Fmental-health-care-therapy-counselling-affordable-startups-india-online%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprioritise%20wellbeing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20HR%20experts%20who%20design%20employee-friendly%20policies%2C%20employers%20who%20champion%20flexible%20work%20cultures%2C%20and%20mental%20health%20organisations%20that%20collaborate%20with%20companies%20to%20foster%20overall%20wellness.%20Their%20insights%20provide%20valuable%20answers%20to%20building%20healthier%2C%20more%20supportive%20workplaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECompanies%20that%20walk%20the%20talk%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20us%20dedicate%20our%20lives%20to%20work%2C%20often%20without%20realising%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20missing%20out%20on%20precious%20time%20with%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20ourselves.%20Roshne%20Balasubramanian%20%E2%80%94%20a%20former%20journalist%20and%20now%20senior%20manager%20of%20communications%20at%20the%20Nalandaway%20Foundation%2C%20a%20non-profit%20organisation%20%E2%80%94%20admits%20to%20having%20done%20the%20same%20in%20her%20previous%20roles.%20She%20worked%20in%20toxic%20environments%20that%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20both%20her%20mental%20and%20physical%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20her%20mother%20fell%20ill%2C%20Roshne%20was%20forced%20to%20reassess%20her%20priorities%2C%20ultimately%20leaving%20journalism.%20She%20describes%20Nalandaway%20as%20a%20refreshing%20change%2C%20where%20employee%20well-being%20is%20truly%20valued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FCopy-of-Infographic-website-2-1727184704.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt