velopment-3-1726670406-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fsocial-development-3-1726670406-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fsocial-development-3-1726670406-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366607%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Percy%20Barnevik%20and%20Dr%20Kalpana%20Sankar%20have%20been%20reaching%20out%20to%20rural%20communities%20across%20India%20through%20Hand%20in%20Hand%20India%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20day.%20A%20call%20from%20one%20of%20the%20children%20%E2%80%94%20informing%20her%20about%20a%20job%20they%20have%20secured%20or%20sharing%20a%20life%20event%20with%20her%20%E2%80%94%20manages%20to%20light%20up%20Dr%20Sankar%E2%80%99s%20mood.%20Point%20this%20out%20to%20her%20and%20she%20says%20it%20is%20all%20the%20validation%20she%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20Meera%E2%80%99s%20story%20for%20instance.%20Meera%20was%20identified%20by%20the%20Child%20Labour%20Elimination%20Programme%20(CLEP)%20field%20staff%20in%202013.%20The%20family%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98scheduled%20tribe%E2%80%99%20status%20meant%20they%20were%20ostracised%20from%20society%20and%20Meera%20and%20her%20siblings%20were%20compelled%20to%20take%20up%20odd%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20working%20at%20brick%20kilns%2C%20cutting%20forest%20wood%2C%20and%20grazing%20cattle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hand%20in%20Hand%20India%20team%20encouraged%20Meera%E2%80%99s%20parents%20to%20enrol%20her%20and%20her%20three%20siblings%20at%20the%20Dhamaneri%20Residential%20Special%20Training%20Centre%20(RSTC)%20in%20Tiruvallur%20district.%20The%20team%20then%20coaxed%20Meera%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F359001%2Fias-officer-balika-panchayat-nanded-maharashtra-young-girls-fight-alcoholis